<?php die('Unauthorized access.'); ?>a:39:{s:2:"id";s:2:"20";s:4:"type";s:8:"document";s:11:"contentType";s:9:"text/html";s:9:"pagetitle";s:22:"Next Steps with Christ";s:9:"longtitle";s:46:"So You Have Received Christ as Lord, Now What?";s:11:"description";s:0:"";s:5:"alias";s:10:"next_steps";s:15:"link_attributes";s:0:"";s:9:"published";s:1:"1";s:8:"pub_date";s:1:"0";s:10:"unpub_date";s:1:"0";s:6:"parent";s:1:"1";s:8:"isfolder";s:1:"1";s:9:"introtext";s:0:"";s:7:"content";s:1006:"<p class="center" style="text-align: right"><img align="middle" alt="Lost and Trying to Find the Right Way to Go" class="center" height="200" src="assets/images/lost.JPG" title="Lost and Trying to Find the Right Way to Go" width="251" /> </p><p>Having received Christ as your personal Lord and Savior there are a few things you should do next.  The first and easiest step to take is to pray.  Prayer is your one-to-one communication with God.  Through your prayer you can ask God for guidance as you begin to read the Bible.  You can also ask him to lead you to a local church where you can continue to be encouraged by like-minded believers and begin to grow spiritually.  Finally, you can become a witness to what God has done for you.  Please take the time to read more about each of these steps as you begin your journey with Christ. </p><p>If you would like to receive further information feel free to <a href="[~18~]">contact us</a> and someone will help encourage you as you take the next steps.</p>";s:8:"richtext";s:1:"1";s:8:"template";s:1:"5";s:9:"menuindex";s:1:"6";s:10:"searchable";s:1:"1";s:9:"cacheable";s:1:"1";s:9:"createdby";s:1:"1";s:9:"createdon";s:10:"1252788167";s:8:"editedby";s:1:"1";s:8:"editedon";s:10:"1291177220";s:7:"deleted";s:1:"0";s:9:"deletedon";s:1:"0";s:9:"deletedby";s:1:"0";s:11:"publishedon";s:10:"1252805037";s:11:"publishedby";s:1:"1";s:9:"menutitle";s:46:"So You Have Received Christ as Lord, Now What?";s:7:"donthit";s:1:"0";s:11:"haskeywords";s:1:"0";s:11:"hasmetatags";